  "description": [
    "TWO AN OPEN LETTER TO AMERICA At Last a Competent Witness Reports the Truth About the Condition and Purpose of the Russian People Answers Convincingly the Tory Lies Circulated Throughout the World to Discredit and Destroy the Soviet Republic and Solemnly Warns the Allies That Armed Intervention Means the Crushing of Russian Democracy and Loss of the War NEW YORKArthur Ransome Russian resident correspondent for many years of The London Daily News publishes in the current number of The New Republic an impassioned plea to the American government and people not to per mit armed intervention by allied troops in Russia Mr Ransome declares the only purpose of such intervention would be to crush the republic of the soviets which is he states the authentic expression of the masses of the Russian people His letter one of the most re markable documents evoked by the great war follows in full Revolutions are not definite politi cal act carried out by the majority in a nation who are unanimous in de siring a single definite object Revo lutionaries and their historians often try to give them that character after wards but that I only an illustration of mans gemeral tendency to"
  ],
